data.enText: more than is necessary, reasonable or acceptable

data.chText: 你生活中的压力太大吗？
data.enText: Are you suffering from an excess of stress in your life?

data.chText: 我一时热情过度答应了工作到很晚。
data.enText: In an excess of enthusiasm I agreed to work late.

data.chText: 凡超量的你都可以扔掉。
data.enText: You can throw away any excess.

data.chText: 他失业后便开始酗酒了。
data.enText: He started drinking to excess after losing his job.

data.chText: 增加幅度不会超过百分之二。
data.enText: The increase will not be in excess of (= more than) two per cent.
an amount by which sth is larger than sth else

data.chText: 我们最多支付600英镑的费用，超过的部分由你支付。
data.enText: We cover costs up to £600 and then you pay the excess.
the part of an insurance claim that a person has to pay while the insurance company pays the rest

data.chText: 本保险单每次索赔均有 100 英镑的免赔额。
data.enText: There is an excess of £100 on each claim under this policy.
extreme behaviour that is unacceptable, illegal or immoral

data.chText: 我们需要新闻自由来约束政府的越轨行为。
data.enText: We need a free press to curb government excesses.

data.chText: 超额的；额外的；附加的；过度的
data.enText: in addition to an amount that is necessary, usual or legal

data.chText: 多余的食物作为脂肪贮存起来。
data.enText: Excess food is stored as fat.

data.chText: 血液里酒精含量过高时驾车是严重的违法行为。
data.enText: Driving with excess alcohol in the blood is a serious offence.

example: the child was spoiled by overindulgence

tr: immoderation as a consequence of going beyond sufficient or permitted limits
a quantity much larger than is needed
the state of being more than full
more than is needed, desired, or required
example: found some extra change lying on the dresser
yet another book on heraldry might be thought redundant
skills made redundant by technological advance
it was supererogatory of her to gloat
extra ribs as well as other supernumerary internal parts
surplus cheese distributed to the needy

value.boxr_value: The noun is pronounced /ɪk'ses/. The adjective is pronounced /'ekses/. 名词读作 /ɪk'ses/，形容词读作 /'ekses/。

value.def: An excess of something is a larger amount than is needed, allowed, or usual.

example.ex: An excess of house plants in a small flat can be oppressive...
example.tran: 在小公寓中摆放过多室内植物会让人觉得很压抑。

example.ex: Polyunsaturated oils are essential for health. Excess is harmful, however.
example.tran: 多不饱和油对健康很重要。但是，食用过量就会有害。

value.def: Excess is used to describe amounts that are greater than what is needed, allowed, or usual.

example.ex: After cooking the fish, pour off any excess fat...
example.tran: 烹完鱼后，倒掉多余的油。

example.ex: The major reason for excess weight is excess eating.
example.tran: 体重超标的主要原因是饮食过量。

value.def: Excess is behaviour that is unacceptable because it is considered too extreme or immoral.

example.ex: She said she was sick of her life of excess.
example.tran: 她说她厌倦了自己无节制的生活。

example.ex: ...the bloody excesses of warfare and empire-building.
example.tran: 战争和帝国扩张的血腥暴行

value.def: Excess is used to refer to additional amounts of money that need to be paid for services and activities that were not originally planned or taken into account.

example.ex: ...a letter demanding an excess fare of £20...
example.tran: 要求额外付20英镑邮资的信

example.ex: Staff who have to travel farther can claim excess travel expenses.
example.tran: 需要到更远的地方出差的职员可以领取额外差旅费。

value.def: The excess on an insurance policy is a sum of money which the insured person has to pay towards the cost of a claim. The insurance company pays the rest.

example.ex: The company wanted £1,800 for a policy with a £500 excess for under-21s.
example.tran: 那家公司想要办理单价1,800英镑的保单，并且要求21岁以下人员承担价值500英镑的免赔额。

value.tran: （保险中的）免赔额，承保人本人需承担的款额

value.def: In excess of means more than a particular amount.

example.ex: Avoid deposits in excess of £20,000 in any one account...
example.tran: 单一账户存款勿超过两万英镑。

example.ex: The energy value of dried fruits is considerably in excess of that of fresh items.
example.tran: 干果的能量值大大超过新鲜水果。

value.def: If you do something to excess, you do it too much.

example.ex: I was reasonably fit, played a lot of tennis, and didn't smoke or drink to excess...
example.tran: 我相当健康，经常打网球，不怎么吸烟，也不酗酒。

example.ex: Red meat, eaten to excess, is very high in fat and calories.
example.tran: 过量食用的红肉中脂肪和卡路里含量很高。
